ADDITIONAL DISCLAIMERS:

1. LEGAL COMPLIANCE:
   This software provides guidance based on publicly available government Standard
   Operating Procedures (SOPs) for cybercrime reporting in India. Users are solely
   responsible for verifying all information with official government portals
   (cybercrime.gov.in, cert-in.org.in, etc.).

2. NOT LEGAL ADVICE:
   This software does NOT constitute legal advice. For legal matters, consult a
   qualified lawyer or legal professional. The creators and contributors are not
   liable for any legal consequences arising from the use of this software.

3. EMERGENCY SITUATIONS:
   In emergencies, always contact official helplines directly:
   - Financial Fraud: 1930 (24x7)
   - Women's Helpline: 181 (24x7)
   - Child Helpline: 1098 (24x7)
   - Emergency: 112 (24x7)

4. DATA PRIVACY:
   While this software is designed for local operation with no external data
   transmission, users are responsible for ensuring compliance with applicable
   data protection laws (IT Act 2000, GDPR, etc.) in their deployment.

5. GOVERNMENT AFFILIATION:
   This is an independent open-source project and is NOT affiliated with,
   endorsed by, or sponsored by the Government of India, CERT-In, Ministry of
   Electronics and IT (MeitY), or any government agency.

6. USE AT YOUR OWN RISK:
   The software is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. The authors
   and contributors shall not be held liable for any damages, losses, or
   consequences arising from the use or misuse of this software.

7. ACCURACY OF INFORMATION:
   While every effort is made to ensure accuracy of SOPs and official links,
   government procedures may change. Users should always verify current
   procedures on official government websites.

8. MODEL LIMITATIONS:
   The AI model (Mistral 7B) may occasionally generate incorrect, incomplete,
   or hallucinated information. Users must exercise critical judgment and
   verify all guidance with official sources.

